Population Research (Wiesbaden). This study comprises the National Questionnaire 
Survey of the German Cardiovascular Prevention Study (1984-86) and a mortality 
follow-up (1998). Included are 7240 persons with German nationality aged 31-69 
years at baseline. 957 persons (13.2%) died during the observation period from 
