We retrospectively studied the outcomes of adult patients with cystic fibrosis 
(CF) hospitalized for severe pulmonary exacerbations (69 cases) between January 
1997 and June 2001. Cases were treated either in the Pulmonary Department (n = 
46) or in the intensive care unit (ICU) (n = 23) depending on severity. 
Noninvasive mechanical ventilation was used in 61% (14 of 23) and 33% (15 of 46) 
