Reconciling heart disease mortality and ICD codes.

Smith DP(1), Bradshaw B.

Author information:
(1)University of Texas School of Public Health, W206, 1200 Herman Pressler, 
Houston, TX 77025, USA. David.P.Smith@uth.tmc.edu

This study uses 61 years of death certificates for Bexar County, Texas, 
uniformly coded under ICD 9, to describe the transition in heart disease 
mortality from 1935-1995. We find that life expectancy for persons dying with 
heart diseases increased throughout this period, with clear differences in rates 
of increase for males and females, associated with acute ischemic heart disease. 
Our data point to an epidemic of AIHD in the 1950s and 1960s, which is now 
abating. Findings are less clear for chronic ischemic heart disease, while other 
